actions.message:
Members of Psycho Gamers Discord server must follow all the rules and guidelines listed below. If any member breaks a rule, they will either be warned or permanently banned depending on the level of violation.
Here is list of all the offenses for which users will be permanently banned:
1) Using inappropriate, offensive or sexually explicit nicknames/profile pictures. You also cannot have a blank nickname.
2) Sending messages which are racist, sexist, homophobic, inappropriate, offensive or vulgar. Sending messages which contain hate speech.
3) Imitating a moderator, developer, or any other user by changing your username/profile picture to match them.
4) Tagging female users for no reason or annoying them. If we get a complaint from any female user that someone from the server is messing with them in DMs, we will investigate the situation and permanently ban the abuser.
5) Sending links which contain malware/virus/phishing or any other harmful links.
6) Using alternate accounts in any tournament.

If you have been banned from the server, you can appeal to us in 3 months, requesting for an unban. However, there is no guarantee that we will remove the ban. The situation will be carefully examined by the mods and they will decide the outcome.

actions.message:
Here is list of all the offenses for which users will receive a warning:
1) Posting any pornographic or NSFW/NSFL content whatsoever.
2) Using inappropriate, offensive or sexually explicit statuses. You will only be warned one time for this.
3) Behaving in a negative or derogatory manner.
4) Spamming text channels or sending messages in caps for no reason.
5) Abusing voice channels or creating a noisy environment in them.
6) Trolling or baiting of any kind.
7) Pinging Psycho Gamer staff members unless they are actively engaging in the conversation.
8) Tagging moderators for no reason.

Users will be automatically banned after receiving more than 5 warnings.
